<br>
To respond to your second request, I think Brutas came pretty close with the below quote in regards to 'what religion should be worshiped'. Or rather, what is an acceptable religion to worship in the US.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> <br>
Generalities such as love, truth, discipline, empathy etc….. are acceptable in my opinion. The above ’prayer’ brings attention to some very neglected issues. The prayer has a positive intention however it does get a little too descriptive for the Non-Christian..... <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think that more attention needs to be given to what constitutes a religion....an 'acceptable religion to be worshiped'. Any modern religion that requires the sacrifice of humans or animals should not be allowed or accepted as a religion IMO. <br>
<br>
As for your first request...the government should not sponsor any form of religion. However, every citizen should be free to worship an acceptable religion anywhere....on private property or state property and be able to vocalize it. Obviously one cannot burst out in class and begin to worship causing a disturbance.<br>
<br>
FIRST-AMENDMENT (Excerpt) <br>
Congress shall make no law respecting an establishment of religion, or prohibit the free exercise thereof: <br>
