<br>
Yes, Brutas does make a compelling point. So let's substitute "Satanism" with the Wiccan religion which is regarded as very peacefull and loving. Make a difference?<br>
<br>
Also, I find it difficult to accept the phrase "acceptable religion in the US". What counts as "acceptable"? For instance, I do not find the attrocities or laws spelled out in the Old Testament at all acceptable and wouldn't want my children to be taught they are OK because God said so.<br>
<br>
I also don't find the story of Christ's death acceptable as told in the New Testament. I surely don't want my children to have to read that violent tale.<br>
<br>
I suppose we could claim that the "majority religion" is acceptable, but the counter argument is if Satanism was the "majority" religion, then would it truly be acceptable?<br>
<br>
<i>"...and be able to vocalize it."</i><br>
<br>
Truly, that is not the issue. What is the issue is when those in public power over others vocalize their religious beliefs. That is an abuse of power and counts as a "sponsored religion". It is the holding up of one religion over all others from a position of public power that is wrong and is not constitutional. Such actions are no longer the domain of free speech but become an abuse of power. <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uquath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 40<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/28/02 10:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=27>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple, Clear and Poweful</span><hr size=1> Here are a few prayers I dug up after a quick search.  If any school broadcast either prayer, I am sure most parents would be outraged and demand for it to stop.  Yet if the prayer were a Christian prayer, it would just be accepted and people that complained would be seen as troublemakers.<br>
