Completely true. I remember in the 1980s the "Zion Coptic Church" of Miami suing the State of Florida over drug busts, because according to them smoking weed was their religion. The so-called "church" lost. hehehe<br>
<br>
Quath,<br>
<br>
<i>"However, instead of laws, I think it should based on not infringing other people's rights."</i><br>
<br>
The problem is with what we mean by "rights". In a democracy, <i>liberty</i> means that everyone has certain rights that can't be taken away by a majority. In the US those <i>rights</i> are defined by the "Bill of Rights". Essentially, it is the Bill of Rights in the US that defines what counts as a "just claim" against others (including the government).<br>
<br>
Legislated morality laws will stay on the books just so long as there is nothing that indicates a violation of judicial interpretation of the Bill of Rights. What that means is that if my city has a law forbidding my running naked through city streets, then I have no right to do so unless I can prove in a court that the law unjustly infringes upon my civil liberties as granted through the Bill of Rights. In short, I would have to prove that public nudity is protected, for example.<br>
<br>
You probably already knew all that, I just wanted to share my thoughts any hoo. :) <p><center><font face="arial" color="CCFFFF">Lurikeen Mali'Kyre</FONT></center><center><table style='Filter: Shadow(Color=#150517, Direction=225)'><tr><td><span class='Necromancer'><font size=2 color="red" face="arial"><i>NECROMANCER</span></td></tr></table></font></i></center><center><font face=arial></center><center><I>"My eyes will pierce your soul, then I will take your life!"</I></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uquath.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#E9D756>(5/29/02 1:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=37>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Simple, Clear and Poweful</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> What that means is that if my city has a law forbidding my running naked through city streets, then I have no right to do so unless I can prove in a court that the law unjustly infringes upon my civil liberties as granted through the Bill of Rights. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
